        }
      ],
      "kind": "declarations"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The property’s default value is ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit/PhysicsBodyMode/dynamic",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ", which means",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "the physics body responds to forces and can collide with all other",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "physics bodies in the simulation.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "Improve the performance of your app by applying ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "code": "dynamic",
                  "type": "codeVoice"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "mode to the physics bodies for just entities that need to interact with",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "all other physics bodies, because each dynamic physics body can be",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "computationally expensive.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Important",
          "style": "important",
          "type": "aside"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "To configure the physics body so that an entity can move around the",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "simulation without reacting to forces, set the property to",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit/PhysicsBodyMode/kinematic",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ". Apps typically use",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "kinematic mode for entities the app programmatically controls,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "such as in response to a control or a person’s interaction.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "For entities that don’t need to move at all, set its physics body’s mode",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "to ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit/PhysicsBodyMode/static",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Physics bodies in ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "static",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " or ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "kinematic",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " mode can’t collide with other",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "physics bodies with either mode, by default.",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "Optionally, you can add collision support for entities that have a",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "physics body in either static or kinematic mode by adding a",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit/PhysicsSimulationComponent",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " to an entity that’s a common ancestor to",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "the entities you want to collide. Then you can set",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit/PhysicsSimulationComponent/CollisionOptions-swift.struct",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " to your preference.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "You can change the mode of an entity’s physics body at any time, but",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "changing it from ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "static",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " to another mode can affect your app’s performance",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "because the transition to a non-static mode can trigger the simulation",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "to rebuild its state.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "Set the mode of an entity’s physics body to ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "code": "static",
                  "type": "codeVoice"
                },
                {
                  "text": " if you know",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": "the entity doesn’t ever need to move; otherwise, set the mode to",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "text": " ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "code": "kinematic",
                  "type": "codeVoice"
                },
                {
                  "text": " or ",
                  "type": "text"
                },
                {
                  "code": "dynamic",
                  "type": "codeVoice"
                },
                {
                  "text": ", even if the entity isn’t currently moving.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Tip",
          "style": "tip",
          "type": "aside"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
